3.00	Bernie_Moore	Bernie Moore	Bernie H. Moore (April 30, 1895 – November 6, 1967) was an American college football, basketball, track and field coach and college athletics administrator. He served as the head football coach at Mercer University (1926–1928) and Louisiana State University (1935–1947). Moore was also the head basketball coach at Mercer (1926–1928) and the head track and field coach at LSU (1930–1947). He was inducted into the College Football Hall of Fame in 1952.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a2/Bernie_Moore.jpg/220px-Bernie_Moore.jpg
